{"title":"Some Tips and Errors in Python","date":"2020-06-21T14:55:50.000Z","date_formatted":{"ll":"Jun 21, 2020","L":"06/21/2020","MM-DD":"06-21"},"link":"2020/06/21/Some-Tips-and-Errors-in-Python","tags":["Python"],"updated":"2020-06-21T14:58:20.987Z","content":"<h1 id=\"1-Error-While-iterating-a-list\">1 Error While iterating a list<a href=\"2020/06/21/Some-Tips-and-Errors-in-Python#1-Error-While-iterating-a-list\"></a></h1><p>When you want to remove something from a list, perhaps iterating it is your first choice. But there are some trouble about it.</p>\n\n\n<figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\">#Example</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">a=[<span class=\"number\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\">3</span>,<span class=\"number\">4</span>,<span class=\"number\">5</span>]</span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"keyword\">for</span> i <span class=\"keyword\">in</span> a:</span><br><span class=\"line\">    a.remove(i)</span><br><span class=\"line\">print(a)</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n<p>it’s result is:</p>\n<p>[2, 4]</p>\n<p>surprise？ that‘s because when you remove the first element of a, a’s length has changed. All of elements after the first one will move forward.</p>\n<p>Solution：</p>\n<figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">a=[<span class=\"number\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\">3</span>,<span class=\"number\">4</span>,<span class=\"number\">5</span>]</span><br><span class=\"line\">t=<span class=\"number\">0</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"keyword\">while</span>(t&lt;len(a)):</span><br><span class=\"line\">    a.pop(t)</span><br><span class=\"line\">print(a)</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n<p>it’s result is:</p>\n<p>[]</p>\n<p>done!</p>\n<h1 id=\"2-Permutation-and-combination-in-Python\">2 Permutation and combination in Python<a href=\"2020/06/21/Some-Tips-and-Errors-in-Python#2-Permutation-and-combination-in-Python\"></a></h1><p>Sometimes we need to use exhaustion, especially in permutation and combination problems. We can do like this:</p>\n<figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br><span class=\"line\">7</span><br><span class=\"line\">8</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\">#Example</span></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"keyword\">import</span> itertools</span><br><span class=\"line\">string = input(<span class=\"string\">\"please input a string:\"</span>)</span><br><span class=\"line\">lst=[]</span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"keyword\">for</span> i <span class=\"keyword\">in</span> range(<span class=\"number\">1</span>, len(string)+<span class=\"number\">1</span>):</span><br><span class=\"line\">    lst1 = [<span class=\"string\">''</span>.join(x) <span class=\"keyword\">for</span> x <span class=\"keyword\">in</span> itertools.permutations(string, i)]</span><br><span class=\"line\">    lst+=lst1</span><br><span class=\"line\">print(lst)</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n<h1 id=\"3-How-to-Use-setup-py-file-in-Github\">3 How to Use setup.py file in Github<a href=\"2020/06/21/Some-Tips-and-Errors-in-Python#3-How-to-Use-setup-py-file-in-Github\"></a></h1><figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">python setup.py install</span><br><span class=\"line\">python setup.py build</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n<h1 id=\"4-Transform-elements-from-a-list-to-keys-of-dict\">4 Transform elements from a list to keys of dict<a href=\"2020/06/21/Some-Tips-and-Errors-in-Python#4-Transform-elements-from-a-list-to-keys-of-dict\"></a></h1><p>dict.fromkeys(seq[, value])</p>\n<p>seq  is the name of your list.</p>\n<p>value is the elements of list.</p>\n<p>This is used to create a new dict variable.</p>\n<h2 id=\"Usage-1-Not-specify-value\">Usage 1: Not specify value<a href=\"2020/06/21/Some-Tips-and-Errors-in-Python#Usage-1-Not-specify-value\"></a></h2><figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">x =(<span class=\"string\">'key1'</span>, <span class=\"string\">'key2'</span>, <span class=\"string\">'key3'</span>)</span><br><span class=\"line\">thisdict = dict.fromkeys(x)</span><br><span class=\"line\">print(thisdict)</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\">#result</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">&#123;<span class=\"string\">'key1'</span>:<span class=\"literal\">None</span>,<span class=\"string\">'key2'</span>:<span class=\"literal\">None</span>,<span class=\"string\">'key3'</span>:<span class=\"literal\">None</span>&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n<h2 id=\"Usage-2-Specify-value\">Usage 2: Specify value<a href=\"2020/06/21/Some-Tips-and-Errors-in-Python#Usage-2-Specify-value\"></a></h2><figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">seq = (<span class=\"string\">'name'</span>, <span class=\"string\">'age'</span>, <span class=\"string\">'sex'</span>)</span><br><span class=\"line\">dict = dict.fromkeys(seq, <span class=\"number\">10</span>)</span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"keyword\">print</span> (<span class=\"string\">\"the new dict is: %s\"</span> %  str(dict)).</span><br><span class=\"line\"></span><br><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"comment\">#result</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">the new dict <span class=\"keyword\">is</span>: &#123;<span class=\"string\">'age'</span>: <span class=\"number\">10</span>, <span class=\"string\">'name'</span>: <span class=\"number\">10</span>, <span class=\"string\">'sex'</span>: <span class=\"number\">10</span>&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n<h2 id=\"Tips-Duplicate-Removal\">Tips (Duplicate Removal)<a href=\"2020/06/21/Some-Tips-and-Errors-in-Python#Tips-Duplicate-Removal\"></a></h2><figure class=\"highlight\"><div><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">a = [<span class=\"number\">1</span>, <span class=\"number\">2</span>, <span class=\"number\">4</span>, <span class=\"number\">2</span>, <span class=\"number\">4</span>, <span class=\"number\">5</span>, <span class=\"number\">6</span>, <span class=\"number\">5</span>, <span class=\"number\">7</span>, <span class=\"number\">8</span>, <span class=\"number\">9</span>, <span class=\"number\">0</span>]</span><br><span class=\"line\">b = &#123;&#125;</span><br><span class=\"line\">b = b.fromkeys(a)</span><br><span class=\"line\">c = list(b.keys())</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>\n\n","next":{"title":"Operating csv files in Python","link":"2020/06/21/Operating-csv-files-in-Python"},"plink":"https://thswind.github.io/2020/06/21/Some-Tips-and-Errors-in-Python/","toc":[{"title":"1 Error While iterating a list","id":"1-Error-While-iterating-a-list","index":"1"},{"title":"2 Permutation and combination in Python","id":"2-Permutation-and-combination-in-Python","index":"2"},{"title":"3 How to Use setup.py file in Github","id":"3-How-to-Use-setup-py-file-in-Github","index":"3"},{"title":"4 Transform elements from a list to keys of dict","id":"4-Transform-elements-from-a-list-to-keys-of-dict","index":"4","children":[{"title":"Usage 1: Not specify value","id":"Usage-1-Not-specify-value","index":"4.1"},{"title":"Usage 2: Specify value","id":"Usage-2-Specify-value","index":"4.2"},{"title":"Tips (Duplicate Removal)","id":"Tips-Duplicate-Removal","index":"4.3"}]}],"reward":true,"copyright":{"custom":"禁止转载-非商用-THSWind"}}